shares-playbook-amazon-owned-grocer-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhole%20Foods%20CEO%20Jason%20Buechel%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20CNBC%20Make%20it%20that%20his%20least%20favorite%20employee%20in%20the%20workplace%20is%20the%20know-it-all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomebody%20who%20thinks%20they%20know%20the%20answer%20to%20absolutely%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Buechel%20told%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BSomebody%20who%20thinks%20that%20it%20has%20to%20be%20exactly%20like%20this%20because%20this%20has%20always%20happened%20before.%20It's%20always%20going%20to%20happen%20this%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-whole-foods%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20grocery%20chain%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20being%20open%20to%20other%20people's%20ideas%20is%20crucial%20for%20career%20growth.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20admitted%20in%20the%20interview%20that%20he%20faced%20a%20similar%20pitfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20sometimes%20could%20have%20been%20that%20person%20in%20my%20past%2C%20on%20certain%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Buechel%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20that%20you%20have%20to%20be%20flexible%2C%20especially%20in%20today's%20world.%20Our%20customers'%20demands%20are%20changing%20all%20the%20time%2C%20things%20are%20always%20changing%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECareer%20experts%20agree%20that%20being%20open%20to%20new%20ideas%20and%20flexibility%20is%20important%20for%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F12-secrets-to-being-a-better-and-more-innovative-boss-2013-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evirtue%20also%20should%20be%20applied%20to%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20equally%20critical%20for%20leadership%20to%20be%20open%20to%20new%20ways%20of%20doing%20things%20and%20to%20support%20their%20teams%20in%20implementing%20i