Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221374%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20financial%20planner%20Anna%20N'Jie-Konte.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20courtesy%20of%20Anna%20N'Jie-Konte%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20have%20many%20wealthy%20financial%20planning%20clients%2C%20and%20they%20all%20share%20four%20habits.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20keep%20a%20long-term%20view%20of%20their%20finances%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20worry%20about%20market%20fluctuations.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20also%20make%20a%20plan%20and%20stick%20to%20it%2C%20and%20invest%20automatically%20in%20good%20times%20and%20bad.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20not%20take%20long%20for%20those%20of%20us%20who%20work%20in%20wealth%20management%20to%20notice%20certain%20commonalities%20among%20our%20clients%3A%20how%20they%20spend%20their%20time%2C%20what%20they%20prioritize%2C%20and%20what%20they%20avoid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20background%20or%20age%2C%20there%20are%20four%20things%20my%20millionaire%20clients%20do%20almost%20universally%2C%20which%20I%20believe%20are%20the%20reasons%20they're%20able%20to%20build%20wealth%20(which%20is%20hard%20enough)%20and%20stay%20wealthy%20(which%20is%20harder%20than%20it%20sounds).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20They%20maintain%20a%20long-term%20focus%20on%20their%20finances%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20easy%20to%20get%20sucked%20into%20day-to-day%20market%20swings%20and%20financial%20temptations.%20The%20financial%20media%20can%20be%20a%20noisy%20place%20that%20advocates%20short-term%20focus%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that%20be%20on%20quarterly%20earnings%2C%20the%20latest%20technical%20chart%20predictions%2C%20or%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair's%20comments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20of%20those%20may%20have%20meaningful%20systemic%20impacts%20on%20the%20market%20or%20an%20individual%20investor's%20portfolio%2C%20most%20millionaires%20know%20they%20need%20to%20ignore%20the%20short-term%20chatter%20and%20focus%20on%20their%20personalized%20long-term%20investment%20hypothesis%20and%20allocation%20with%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advisors%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20prevents%20them%20from%20making%20emotionally%20driven%20mistakes%2C%20such%20as%20market%20timing%20and%20herding%20behavior%2C%20that%20can%20potentially%20cost%20them%20thousands%20or%20millions%20of%20dollars%20over%20the%20long%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20simply%2C%20they%20have%20a%20long-term%20plan%20that%20they%20keep%20in%20front%20of%20mind%20when%20making%20daily%20decisions.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20They%20make%20a%20plan%2C%20then%20save%20and%20invest%20accordingly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20least-sexy%20aspects%20of%20wealth-building%20are%20saving%2C%20investing%2C%20and%20paying%20off%20debt%20before%20you%20do%20anything%20else.%20Despite%20the%20fact%20that%20these%20things%20are%20boring%2C%20they%20are%20the%20most%20surefire%20ways%20to%20achieve%20financial%20abundance.%20They%20aren't%20magic%3B%20they%20simply%20ensure%20you%20are%20living%20within%20your%20means%2C%20building%20wealth%20consistently%20through%20monthly%20contributions%2C%20and%20making%20progress%20toward%20your%20financial%20goals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20found%20that%20my%20successful%20clients%20decide%20what%20they%20want%20to%20achieve%2C%20how%20much%20they%20need%20to%20save%20and%20invest%20to%20achieve%20their%20goals%20in%20the%20desired%20timeline%2C%20and%20then%20structure%20their%20lifestyle%20around%20that.%20This%20has%20the%20super-stealth%20benefit%20of%20meaning%20you%20have%20to%20save%20less%20in%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20you're%20living%20on%20a%20smaller%20percentage%20of%20your%20income.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20They%20invest%20automatically%20in%20the%20good%20times%20and%20bad%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20millionaire%20secrets%20is%20that%20they%20often%20ignore%20the%20temporary%20market%20swings%20and%20commit%20to%20investing%20in%20the%20good%20times%20and%20bad.%20They%20determine%20how%20much%20they%20need%20to%20save%20and%20invest%20on%20a%20monthly%20or%20quarterly%20basis%2C%20and%20then%20they%20set%20up%20automatic%20bank%20transfers%20and%20purchase%20plans%20in%20their%20investment%20accounts%20in%20order%20to%20execute%20their%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20automating%20these%20transactions%2C%20they%20ensure%20that%20they%20can%20divorce%20their%20investing%20decisions%20from%20their%20momentary%20emotions.%20There%20is%20less%20temptation%20to%20pause%20contributions%20because%20they%20%26quot%3Bwant%20to%20see%20what%20the%20market%20is%20doing.%26quot%3B%20They%20decide%20beforehand%20what%20needs%20to%20happen%20and%20execute%20that%20carefully%20thought-out%20plan.%20This%20has%20the%20primary%20benefit%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdollar-cost-averaging%5C%22%3Edollar-cost%20averaging%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20shown%20to%20deliver%20superior%20results%20to%20market%20timing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20They're%20apathetic%20to%20market%20swings%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.berkshirehathaway.com%2Fletters%2F1990.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%201990%20shareholder%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Warren%20Buffett%20said%20the%20following%20regarding%20Berkshire%20Hathaway's%20investment%20style%3A%20%26quot%3BLethargy%20bordering%20on%20sloth%20remains%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20our%20investment%20style%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20inherently%20know%20there%20are%20risks%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-invest-in-stocks%5C%22%3Estock%20market%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20but%20stocks%20outperform%20most%20other%20asset%20classes%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20However%2C%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20for%20us%20to%20remove%20the%20emotion%20from%20daily%20market%20swings%20and%20maintain%20a%20long-term%20focus.%20The%20market%20crash%20in%20early%202020%20proved%20that%20it%20is%20much%20more%20difficult%20to%20stay%20invested%20when%20you%20are%20focused%20on%20the%20short%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20my%20millionaire%20clients%20are%20clear%20and%20focused%20on%20what%20their%20individual%20buckets%20of%20money%20are%20supposed%20to%20do%20for%20them%2C%20and%20they%20know%20they%20are%20invested%20accordingly.%20This%20means%20that%20although%20they%20may%20feel%20concerned%2C%20they%20generally%20don't%20panic%20and%20make%20any%20changes%20that%20will%20hinder%20their%20long-term%20portfolio%20growth.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20there%20should%20be%20very%20little%20reason%20to%20check%20your%20portfolio%20in%20a%20volatile%20market%20or%20correction%20because%20it%20should%20be%20appropriately%20invested%20in%20accordance%20with%20your%20investment%20time%20horizon%20and%20risk%20tolerance.%20Most%20of%20the%20frenetic%20energy%20around%20checking%20your%20portfolio%20stems%20from%20those%20two%20boundaries%20not%20being%20settled.%20This%20is%20something%20my%20millionaire%20clients%20fully%20embody%2C%20and%20it%20allows%20them%20to%20see%20the%20fruits%20of%20that%20pre-planning%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompounding%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26