ewing%26quot%3B%20the%20status%20of%20the%20licenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20dozen%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20serve%20alcohol%20on%20the%20premises%20of%20Trump-branded%20or%20Trump-owned%20hotels%20and%20golf%20courses%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nj.gov%2Flps%2Fabc%2Fdownloads%2Fabchandbook02.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20Jersey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsla.ny.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2022%2F05%2Fstateliquorauthority-retaillicenseeshandbookrevised5-6-2022.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dramshopexpert.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F05%2FFlorida-Responsible-Alcoholic-Beverage-Retailers-Handbook.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlorida%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.ca.gov%2Flicensing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20survey%20by%20Business%20Insider%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20states%20prohibit%20felons%20or%20people%20convicted%20of%20%26quot%3Bmoral%26quot%3B%20offenses%20such%20as%20fraud%20from%20holding%20a%20liquor%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20the%20holder%20of%20any%20liquor%20license%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20he%20is%20not%20an%20officer%20or%20director%20of%20any%20entity%20that%20holds%20a%20liquor%20license%20in%20New%20Jersey%20%E2%80%94%20or%20anywhere%20in%20the%20United%20States%20for%20that%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20GOP%20presidential%20frontrunner%20said%20through%20a%20spokesman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20may%20keep%20him%20insulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20may%20not%20be%20responsible%20for%20liquor%20licenses%20held%20in%20the%20name%20of%20his%20tenants%20or%20under%20LLCs%20for%20which%20he%20is%20not%20on%20the%20paperwork%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump's%20name%20is%20not%20connected%20to%20the%20license%2C%20then%20his%20conviction%20could%20be%20moot%2C%20said%20William%20Fay%2C%20a%20former%20New%20Jersey%20deputy%20attorney%20general%20who%20worked%20with%20the%20enforcement%20bureau%20of%20the%20state's%20division%20of%20alcoholic%20beverage%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20because%20Trump's%20name%20is%20in%20the%20title%20of%20the%20LLC%2C%20doesn't%20mean%20he's%20a%20member%20or%20owner%2C%20Fay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20he%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20LLC%2C%20then%20simply%20being%20licensed%20as%20an%20LLC%20wouldn't%20offer%20any%20sort%20of%20protection.%20If%20he's%20not%20a%20member%2C%20it%20could%2C%20Fay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e42a26df-ad9c-4906-bdbc-b94966fbbe4a%5C%22%3EBut%20there%20are%20loopholes%20to%20this%20loophole%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20because%20he%20is%20not%20on%20the%20paperwork%20doesn't%20mean%20he's%20scot-free%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Aaron%20H.%20Pierce%2C%20a%20Manhattan-based%20attorney%20who%20specializes%20in%20alcoholic%20beverage-control%20law%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump-branded%20properties%20in%20Manhattan%20house%20a%20half-dozen%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20that%20serve%20alcohol%2C%20including%20the%20memorabilia-crammed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fempty-classified-folder-on-display-at-trump-tower-bar-msnbc-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B45%20Wine%20%26amp%3B%20Whiskey%20Bar%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Trump%20Tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20Trump%20is%20landlord%20to%20the%20bar%20operators%20at%20one%20of%20these%20properties%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20bar%20operators%20who%20hold%20the%20liquor%20license%2C%20Pierce%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20say%20the%20bar%20is%20owned%20by%20an%20LLC%20for%20which%20Trump%20is%20not%20listed%20as%20a%20director%20or%20officer%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20is%20charging%20the%20bar%20a%20flat%20rent%2C%20his%20felony%20status%20won't%20impact%20that%20liquor%20license.%20But%20if%20he%20is%20directly%20profiting%20from%20liquor%20sales%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20getting%20a%20cut%20of%20the%20bar%20till%20%E2%80%94%20then%20that's%20another%20story%2C%20said%20Pierce%2C%20partner%20at%20the%20business%20law%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpiercekwok.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPierce%20%26amp%3B%20Kwok%20LLP%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20he's%20not%20on%20the%20paperwork%2C%20but%20he's%20profiting%20directly%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20alcohol%2C%20then%20he's%20not%20off%20the%20hook%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20would%20still%20have%20options%2C%20though%2C%20even%20if%20his%20hush-money%20conviction%20voided%20one%20or%20more%20of%20his%20liquor%20licenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%2C%20Trump%20could%20ask%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nycourts.gov%2Fcourthelp%2Fcriminal%2FCRD.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecertificate%20of%20relief%20from%20civil%20disabilities%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Pierce%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3BCRD%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20it's%20called%2C%20would%20be%20issued%20by%20the%20judge%20at%20or%20after%20sentencing%2C%20and%20it%20can%20help%20someone%20with%20a%20conviction%20overcome%20certain%20licensing%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20New%20Jersey%20determines%20that%20Trump's%20hush-money%20conviction%20disqualifies%20him%20as%20a%20licensee%2C%20as%20it's%20a%20crime%20of%20%26quot%3Bmoral%20turpitude%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20could%20divest%20from%20the%20LLC%20that%20owns%20the%20license%2C%20said%20Fay%2C%20the%20former%20prosecutor%20at%20the%20division's%20enforcement%20bureau.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20I%20understand%2C%20it%20involves%20some%20sort%20of%20misrepresentations%2C%20so%20I%20would%20assume%20there's%20some%20fraud%20in%20that%20%E2%80%94%20so%20theoretically%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20moral%20turpitude%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20Fay%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%2C%20yeah%2C%20the%20next%20option%20would%20be%20to%20divest%2