20make%20small%2C%20healthy%20changes%20without%20cutting%20them%20out%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltra-processed%20foods%20are%20such%20a%20big%20part%20of%20our%20diet.%20They're%20convenient%20and%20easy.%20There%20hasn't%20been%20as%20much%20work%20on%20thinking%20about%20not%20just%20the%20type%20of%20food%20but%20also%20how%20it's%20processed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%2C%20published%20June%2011%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.neurology.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1212%2FWNL.0000000000209432%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeurology%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20step%20closer%20to%20helping%20scientists%20understand%20why%20processed%20food%20might%20be%20bad%20for%20our%20health.%20The%20study%20was%20observational%2C%20which%20means%20it%20can't%20directly%20tell%20us%20if%20processed%20food%20caused%20the%20health%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20does%20offer%20hints%20at%20simple%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-ultra-processed-foods-may-be-healthier-than-homemade-scientist-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20healthier%20choices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Kimberly%2C%20who%20offered%20tips%20on%20picking%20more%20nutritious%20snacks%20and%20how%20much%20processed%20food%20you%20should%20aim%20to%20cut%20back%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2274cd1594-15f5-469b-85b5-b3a0681a778f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESwapping%20out%20as%20little%20as%20two%20servings%20of%20processed%20food%20a%20week%20can%20help%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Kimberly%20and%20his%20team%20embarked%20on%20their%20study%2C%20their%20goal%20was%20to%20come%20up%20with%20some%20actionable%20advice%20for%20people.%20Is%20it%20possible%20to%20slightly%20reduce%20processed%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20without%20eliminating%20them%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20and%20meaningfully%20improve%20your%20health%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20research%20suggested%20you%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20study%20found%20that%20a%2010%25%20increase%20in%20processed%20food%20consumption%20was%20linked%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20cognitive%20impairment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20equivalent%20of%20about%20two%20meals%20per%20week.%20The%20research%20team%20based%20their%20analysis%20on%20that%20amount%20because%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20realistic%20amount%20for%20people%20to%20reduce%2C%20and%20an%20easy%20goal%20to%20remember.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20answer%20we%20came%20up%20with%20is%20that%20we%20move%20the%20needle%2C%20and%20we%20can%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20optimism%20from%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Kimberly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDiet%20is%20really%20hard%20to%20change.%20There%20are%20many%20reasons%20we%20eat%20what%20we%20eat%2C%20such%20as%20time%2C%20convenience%2C%20and%20budget%3Cs%3E.%20%3C%2Fs%3EAll%20of%20these%20things%20impact%20the%20dietary%20choices%20we%20make%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a834cd0-28f9-4cec-9901-2697fc1955b4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChoose%20whole%20foods%20high-fiber%20options%20like%20nuts%20and%20seeds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20of%20research%20tell%20us%20that%20processed%20foods%20are%20harmful%20in%20part%20because%20they're%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-protein-processed-food-leads-to-overeating-weight-gain-study-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elacking%20in%20fiber%20and%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20vitamins%20and%20minerals.%20They%20also%20introduce%20unhealthy%20ingredients%20into%20your%20diet%2C%20such%20as%20added%20oil%2C%20sugar%2C%20salt%2C%20and%20preservatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20you%20can't%20offset%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20junk%20food%20diet%20by%20popping%20some%20multivitamins%20or%20gulping%20a%20green%20juice%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20not%20eating%20a%20healthy%20meal%2C%20you're%20also%20eating%20an%20unhealthy%20meal%2C%20so%20the%20evidence%20suggests%20you%20can't%20just%20add%20a%20supplement.%20It's%20both%20sides%20that%20are%20important%20when%20thinking%20about%20brain%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20Kimberly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20replacing%20highly%20processed%20foods%20with%20healthier%20alternatives%20can%20give%20you%20double%20the%20benefits%20because%20you're%20adding%20nutrients%20and%20cutting%20out%20potentially%20harmful%20additives%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20swapping%20French%20fries%20for%20baked%20sweet%20potatoes%20helps%20to%20reduce%20salt%20and%20oil%20in%20your%20diet%20but%20also%20brings%20in%20more%20vitamins%20and%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKimberly's%20research%20has%20inspired%20him%20to%20snack%20on%20nuts%20or%20carrots%20instead%20of%20cookies%20or%20crackers%20%E2%80%94%20cutting%20his%20sugar%20intake%20and%20quickly%20increasing%20the%20amount%20of%20fiber%20in%20his%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20just%20feeding%20ourselves%20when%20we%20eat.%20We're%20feeding%20a%20really%20complicated%20ecosystem%20in%20the%20gut%20that%20helps%20metabolize%20what%20we%20eat%2C%26quot%3B%20Kimberly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2289eb4302-7a5c-4cf0-9d5c-7d71966c6927%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAim%20for%20ingredients%20you%20recognize%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20have%20to%20give%20up%20processed%20foods%20completely%20to%20improve%20your%20health.%20When%20you're%20reaching%20for%20something%20cheap%20and%20convenient%2C%20it%20can%20help%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-foods-with-protein-fiber-better-for-you-expert-says-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echoose%20healthier%20processed%20food%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20recognizable%20ingredients%2C%20according%20to%20Kimberly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20it%20and%20think%2C%20that%20could%20be%20made%20in%20my%20kitchen%2C%20that's%20a%20good%20indicator%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20it%20can%20be%20more%20helpful%20to%20make%20a%20few%20small%20swaps%20you%20can%20stick%20to%20than%20trying%20(and%20failing)%20to%20swear%20off%20processed%20foods%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20perfect%20world%2C%20we%20would%20all%20eat%20unprocessed%20foods%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20Kimberly%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20sprint.%20Short%2C%20big%20changes%20aren't%20the%20goal.%20Even%20modest%20changes%2C%20if%20they're%20sustainable%2C%20can%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-researcher-healthy-swaps-to-cut-processed-foods-improve-brain-gut-health-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718310558000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66688d58764df1611258947f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-researcher-healthy-swaps-to-cut-processed-foods-improve-brain-gut-health-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%20researcher%20who%20studies%20processed%20food%20explains%20why%20he%20stopped%20eating%20certain%20foods%2C%20and%20the%20simple%2C%20healthy%20alternatives%20he%20eats%20instead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-researcher-healthy-swaps-to-cut-processed-foods-improve-brain-gut-health-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Poonam%20sends%20blessings%20to%20Sonakshi%20and%20Zaheer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718310026000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110977723%2Cimgsize-53678.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindi