ip_082919_how-to-use-a-portable-laundry-machine-20%26h%3Daad2f07e34e549adae74333036a708cf7177bbf745967c03dfabd9e124f9b798%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f427c7%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-use-a-portable-washing-machine%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.walmart.com%252Fip%252FSterilite-1-5-Bushel-Ultra-Square-Laundry-Basket-White%252F16351113%253Fselected%253Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESterilite%201.5%20Bushel%20Square%20Laundry%20Basket%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20lightweight%20and%20unobtrusive%2C%20and%20when%20it's%20full%2C%20I%20know%20it's%20time%20to%20run%20a%20load%20of%20laundry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStep%202%3A%20Presoak%20anything%20that%20needs%20special%20treatment%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPortable%20washers%20don't%20have%20all%20the%20bells%20and%20whistles%20that%20a%20full-size%20unit%20has.%20If%20anything%20is%20stained%20or%20needs%20special%20treatment%2C%20do%20it%20first.%20We%20love%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiip_082919_how-to-use-a-portable-laundry-machine-20%26h%3D3b88f7e9a1a17211d8c2711f18cd787677ee5cb781513447107ffd772c316b89%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f427c7%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-use-a-portable-washing-machine%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FOxiClean-Versatile-Stain-Remover-Free%252Fdp%252FB005GI8UPI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOxiClean%20Versatile%20Stain%20Remover%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20we%20find%20it%20helps%20preserves%20color%20and%20gets%20stains%20out%20fast.%20You%20can%20presoak%20your%20clothes%20in%20a%20bucket%2C%20tub%20or%20sink%2C%20or%20even%20in%20the%20body%20of%20the%20washer%20itself.%20My%20washer%20has%20a%20soak%20mode%2C%20but%20you%20can%20also%20just%20fill%20up%20the%20washer%20and%20let%20it%20soak%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStep%203%3A%20Connect%20your%20washer%20to%20the%20tap%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20portable%20washer%20is%20a%20little%20different%2C%20but%20all%20operate%20on%20the%20same%20premise%3A%20an%20inlet%20hose%20that%20connects%20to%20your%20sink%20tap%20to%20fill%20the%20machine%20with%20water%20and%20an%20outflow%20hose%20to%20drain.%20When%20you%20set%20up%20your%20washing%20machine%2C%20you'll%20follow%20manufacturer%20instructions%20to%20connect%20the%20hoses%20to%20the%20body%20of%20your%20machine.%20You'll%20need%20a%20wrench%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20hoses%20are%20connected%20tightly%20to%20the%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnecting%20to%20the%20tap%20takes%20some%20trial%20and%20error%20at%20first.%20The%20tap%20connector%20has%20two%20parts%3A%20a%20quick%20release%20and%20a%20screw-on%20nozzle.%20Using%20your%20fingers%2C%20depress%20the%20quick-release%20valve%20and%20remove%20the%20screw-on%20nozzle.%20Lining%20the%20threads%20of%20the%20nozzle%20up%20with%20the%20threads%20on%20your%20sink%20tap%2C%20screw%20the%20nozzle%20onto%20your%20sink.%20You%20may%20need%20to%20remove%20the%20aerator%20from%20your%20sink%20tap%2C%20if%20it%20has%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20nozzle%20included%20with%20your%20machine%20doesn't%20fit%20your%20sink%20tap%2C%20you%20can%20purchase%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiip_082919_how-to-use-a-portable-laundry-machine-20%26h%3Dc21faa3393ea77896aa8dde47128aba3c2a9e9ab7bcd597c0badf4f5520a5bca%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f427c7%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-use-a-portable-washing-machine%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252FB07DLHYR71%252Fref%253Das_li_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526tag%253Dbiip_082919_how-to-use-a-portable-laundry-machine-20%2526camp%253D1789%2526creative%253D9325%2526linkCode%253Das2%2526creativeASIN%253DB07DLHYR71%2526linkId%253D4e8727ba76b960d140cb500cc8ebf806%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20pack%20of%20adapters%20from%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20see%20what%20works.%20A%20good%20fit%20means%20minimal%20leaking%20from%20the%20area%20around%20the%20nozzle%20(minor%20leaks%20can%20be%20okay).%20Once%20the%20nozzle%20is%20installed%2C%20push%20the%20hose%20with%20the%20quick%20release%20onto%20the%20nozzle%20and%20turn%20the%20water%20on%20at%20the%20tap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStep%204%3A%20Place%20the%20drainage%20tube%20into%20the%20sink%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20reading%20horror%20stories%20of%20drain%20hoses%20slipping%20out%20of%20sinks%20and%20flooding%20floors%2C%20I%20use%20a%20piece%20of%20string%20to%20secure%20the%20outflow%20tube%20to%20the%20sink.%20If%20you're%20using%20your%20bathroom%20sink%20to%20fill%20the%20washer%2C%20you%20may%20choose%20to%20place%20the%20outflow%20in%20your%20bathtub%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStep%205%3A%20Leave%20the%20water%20on%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20load%20of%20laundry%20I%20did%20with%20my%20portable%20washer%2C%20I%20sat%20next%20to%20the%20machine%20and%20turned%20the%20water%20tap%20on%20and%20off%20every%20time%20it%20switched%20from%20filling%20to%20agitating.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%20Leave%20the%20tap%20running%20the%20entire%20cycle.%20Depending%20on%20what%20you're%20washing%20you%20can%20either%20set%20the%20tap%20to%20cold%20or%20hot%20water.%20I%20prefer%20cold%20water%20because%20it's%20easier%20and%20makes%20colors%20less%20likely%20to%20run%2C%20but%20you%20may%20wish%20to%20use%20hot%20water%20for%20undergarments%2C%20sheets%2C%20and%20towels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStep%206%3A%20Turn%20your%20machine%20on%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20need%20an%20extension%20cable%20to%20reach%20your%20nearest%20three-prong%20outlet.%20Plug%20your%20machine%20in%20and%20press%20the%20%26quot%3Bon%26quot%3B%20button.%20Select%20your%20load%20size%20and%20laundry%20mode%2C%20then%20press%20start.%20The%20washer%20should%20immediately%20begin%20filling%20with%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EStep%207%3A%20Add%20detergent%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20portable%20washers%20don't%20have%20detergent%20dispensers%2